# Treesy Travel CO₂ Offset Calculator — Walkthrough

## What Was Built

A client-side web calculator for travel agencies to estimate CO₂ emissions and offset them with Treesy trees. No backend, no API — just open [index.html](file:///d:/TREESY/index.html) in any browser.

### File Structure

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| [index.html](file:///d:/TREESY/index.html) | HTML shell — page structure & layout |
| [styles.css](file:///d:/TREESY/styles.css) | All styling — dark glassmorphism, responsive |
| [app.js](file:///d:/TREESY/app.js) | All logic — cities, emissions, offset slider |

### Key Features
- **80+ cities** with coordinates for Haversine distance calculation
- **5 transport modes**: Flight, Bus, Car, Train, Ferry
- **Hotel stays**: 30.9 kg CO₂/night
- **Real-time recalculation** on every input change
- **Offset slider**: 0–200% + custom exact input
- **"Copy Summary"** button for emailing quotes to clients
- **Methodology footnotes** (DEFRA, EEA sources)

---

## Verification

### Charlie's Example Trip

| Segment | Mode | Distance | CO₂ |
|---------|------|----------|-----|
| Copenhagen → Nairobi | ✈️ Flight | 6,409 km | 1,376 kg |
| Nairobi → Kilimanjaro | ✈️ Flight | 239 km | 129 kg |
| Kilimanjaro → Dar es Salaam | 🚌 Bus | 442 km | 163 kg |
| Dar es Salaam → Copenhagen | ✈️ Flight | 7,366 km | 1,580 kg |
| + 10 hotel nights | 🏨 | — | 309 kg |
| **Total** | | | **3,558 kg CO₂** |

At **100% offset** → **36 trees**
At **150% offset** → **54 trees** (Carbon Positive 🌟)

